programme.desc: Denmark v Republic of Ireland (Kick-off 7.45pm). Coverage of the first leg of the World Cup qualifying play-off, which takes place at Parken Stadium in Copenhagen. These sides haven't met since August 2007, when a friendly encounter in Aarhus finished 4-0 to the visitors. Robbie Keane and Shane Long both scored a brace in that game, and Martin O'Neill will be hoping for a similar result here to increase his team's chances of reaching their first World Cup finals since 2002 in Japan and South Korea(n)

programme.title: A Sporting Chance
programme.desc: Liam Toland and Rosie Foley face an uphill struggle as they try to encourage their charges to commit to their training programme. In an attempt to boost morale, Munster Rugby invites the participants to an evening game, before Liam and Rosie ask them to write about their experience, with the two best essays winning their writers VIP tickets to watch Brian O'Driscoll play in his last home game for Ireland before retirement. Finally, the trainers organise a challenge game for their group, but the training programme hits a major setback when fights break out after the team is badly beaten(n)

programme.title: A Sporting Chance
programme.desc: Only a few weeks remain before the team must head to London, but spirits are low. Liam Toland and Rosie Foley decide a spot of team-building is in order, and take their charges to the race track for some high-speed go-karting. The group also organises an event for a suicide-prevention charity operating in Limerick, and hopes remain that, if their efforts prove successful, the players' confidence will be boosted ahead of the tag rugby tournament(n)

programme.desc: Years after unceremoniously firing Pigman, the guys from Elusive Wildlife come crawling back. As a peace offering, they give Pigman free range to hunt on their property day and night, and it looks like this relationship is built for the long haul(n)

programme.title: Trailing the Hunter's Moon

programme.title: Moment of Impact
programme.desc: James Brion and Rob Dunham take a look back over the years at some of the best hunts from Nebraska. Then, winner of the "Best Buck Ever" contest and elite member John Robbins tries for the biggest buck of his life(n)

programme.title: Jon Baker's Guide 4 Adventure
programme.desc: Kodiak Island blacktail. Jon joins up with Kieth Hilty and Dorian Thompson for some pre-rut action(n)

programme.title: Avian-X TV

programme.title: Avian-X TV
programme.desc: The king of all waterfowl, the canvasback, has a majesty and mystique all it's own. Traveling to Lake St. Clair, Fred joins friends, Tim and Jeff, on a quest threatened by mother nature. Destination: the lake's celery beds for limits of canvasback(n)

programme.title: RNT-V
programme.desc: Johnny wins the Champion of Champions and hear his views on calling ducks, calling judges and call making(n)

programme.title: Mojo Outdoors TV

programme.title: The Honey Brake Experience

programme.title: Outback Outdoors

programme.title: Sheep Shape

programme.title: Country Boys Outdoors

programme.title: Spook Nation
